In a speech at the University of Nevada-Las Vegas, President Joe Biden praised healthcare workers and highlighted the importance of affordable healthcare. He emphasized the role of nurses in saving lives and called them the most underrated profession in America. Biden discussed the Affordable Care Act (Obamacare) and the need to protect it, particularly for people with pre-existing conditions. He outlined his administration's efforts to make healthcare more affordable, such as lowering prescription drug costs and capping out-of-pocket expenses for seniors on Medicare. He also criticized Republicans who want to repeal the Affordable Care Act and cut Social Security and Medicare. Biden stressed the importance of fairness and called for wealthy individuals and corporations to pay their fair share in taxes. He concluded by thanking healthcare professionals for their dedication and urging unity in working towards a better future.